%S A394946 1,1,4,16,74,373,1978,10869,61333,353295,2068790,12278033,73688758,
%T A394946 446463874,2727077153,16775114011,103826794916,646123471060,
%U A394946 4040379305512,25375172238462,159988503980025,1012280466447193,6425493234810251,40905801769356203,261114212851326709
%N A394946 Number of well-formed bracketed words of total length 2n built from the symbol * (of length 2) and three unary bracket types (), [], and {}, with no empty bracket pair, where every maximal chain of unary brackets is written in canonical weakly increasing order.
%C A394946 a(0)=1 counts the empty word.
%C A394946 For n>=1, a(n)=b_{3,2}^c(2n) in the notation of Au and Bremner; see Section 3.
%C A394946 Equivalently, a(n) counts canonical representatives of such bracketed words under commutativity of the three unary bracket types.
%C A394946 In each maximal chain of nested unary brackets, the bracket types are weakly increasing from outermost to innermost.
%C A394946 Equivalently, a(n) counts rooted ordered trees with n vertices in which each leaf represents *, each unary internal node is labeled 1, 2, or 3, every non-unary internal node has at least 2 ordered children, and the labels along every maximal unary chain are weakly increasing from the root toward the leaves.
%C A394946 Equivalently, a(n) counts peakless Schroeder paths of semilength n with three types of up-steps U_1, U_2, U_3, such that along every matched ascent the labels are weakly increasing.
%C A394946 Here a matched ascent is a maximal consecutive block of up-steps whose matching down-steps all belong to the same descent.
%C A394946 Equivalently, a(n) counts rooted ordered binary trees with n vertices in which every right edge is labeled 1, 2, or 3, and along every maximal right-edge chain whose intermediate vertices have no left child, the labels are weakly increasing.
%H A394946 Yu Hin Au and Murray R. Bremner, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.25731">Enumerating Multi-Operator Monomials in Commutative and Noncommutative Settings</a>, arXiv:2604.25731 [math.CO], 2026. See pp. 4, 19 (Table 5).
%F A394946 G.f.: 1 + (1 - 4*x + 3*x^2 - x^3 - sqrt((1-4*x+3*x^2-x^3)^2 - 4*x*(3*x - 3*x^2 + x^3))) / (2*(3*x - 3*x^2 + x^3)) = 1 + A(x).
%F A394946 G.f. satisfies A(x) = x + x*A(x) + (3*x - 3*x^2 + x^3)*(A(x) + A(x)^2).
%F A394946 a(n) = 4*f(n-1) - 3*f(n-2) + f(n-3) + 3*Sum_{k=1..n-2} a(k)*a(n-1-k) - 3*Sum_{k=1..n-3} a(k)*a(n-2-k) + Sum_{k=1..n-4} a(k)*a(n-3-k) with a(0)=a(1)=1 where f(n)=a(n) for n>=1 and f(n)=0 for n<=0.
%e A394946 a(3)=16 = 1 + 9 + 6: one word with no unary operators, namely ***; 9 words with one unary operator, namely P_i(**), P_i(*)*, *P_i(*) for i=1,2,3; and 6 canonical double-unary words P_i(P_j(*)) with 1<=i<=j<=3.
%Y A394946 Cf. A000108, A394945, A394947, A007564.
